The paper deals with graph theory and specifically the chromatic number of graphs, which falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the neighbourhoods of vertices and their impact on the chromatic number, which is a topic in Graph Theory (cs.GT) and Computational Geometry (cs.CG). The paper also provides evidence for the proposed conjecture using fractional relaxation, which is a technique used in Discrete Optimization (cs.DS) and Linear Programming (cs.LG).
